Get Started with Einstein Bots

On the Einstein Bots setup page, turn on bots, create an Einstein bot, and access your list of bots.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To view the Einstein Bot Builder:	

View Setup

OR

Lightning User Experience


To build and manage Einstein Bots:	

Customize Application

OR

Modify Metadata

OR

Manage Bots

Before setting up bots, make sure you meet the Einstein Bots Requirements.

From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Einstein Bots, and then select Einstein Bots.
To get started with Einstein Bots, click the toggle, and accept the terms.
Click New and then follow the guided setup. To start with a basic framework, select Start from Scratch. To create a bot with built-in dialogs that handle many common use cases, select Intro Template. Learn more about the options in Create an Einstein Bot.
After you complete the guided setup, you can edit specific settings about your bot on the Bot Overview Page. Learn more about each setting in Update the Bot Overview Page.
Enable Einstein Bots in a Scratch Org
You can quickly enable Einstein Bots in a scratch org using Salesforce DX.
